1583298000.title: Bargain Hunt
1583298000.descr: Anita Manning travels by steam to the Elsecar Heritage Centre in Yorkshire for today's Bargain Hunt. She's joined by experts Kate Bliss and Jonathan Pratt who'll be helping the reds and blues to bag a bargain that will hopefully make a profit at today's auction with Knutsford auctioneer Nick Hall. Anita also pays a visit to Stockport's Hat Works Museum to find out about the town's hatting heyday.

1583300700.title: Call the Midwife
1583300700.descr: Period drama series set in East London in the 1950s, following the life and work of a young midwife Jenny Lee and her colleagues at the Nonnatus House nursing convent. They serve the poor society of Poplar, London. Their main duty is to help bring safe birth to women and help them look after their newborns.

1583303700.title: New Tricks
1583303700.descr: Popular long-running BBC crime drama about the trials and tribulations of aging officers as they attempt to solve the cold cases of yesteryear while coming to terms with their own years. Over the course of its 12 seasons it charted the work of the Metropolitan Police fictional unsolved crimes department, drawing its title from the adage of not being able to teach old dogs new tricks.

1583307000.title: DIY SOS: The Big Build
1583307000.descr: Take a family in desperate need of help in their home. Add some local tradesmen, lot's of generosity and a bucket load of community spirit. You've got yourself the recipe for DIY SOS. Nick Knowles, along with him team of home improvement experts, and lot's of happy volunteers from the communities of Britain pitch in to make life changing modifications to the homes of families who need them most.
